net.cabezudo.json.values

Class JSONArray

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.cabezudo.json.JSONElement
      • net.cabezudo.json.values.JSONValue<JSONArray>
        • net.cabezudo.json.values.JSONArray
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<JSONArray>, java.lang.Iterable<JSONValue>, JSONable

    public class JSONArray
extends JSONValue<JSONArray>
implements java.lang.Iterable<JSONValue>
    A JSONArray is an object extended from JSONValue object in order to represent a JSON array that can be used to create JSON structures.

    A JSONArray is a list of JSONValue objects that represent the JSON array structure.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(JSONArray jsonArray)
        Compare two array using the size first and compare the elements one by one if the size is the same.

        First a value less than 0 if the size of this JSONArray is less than the size of the JSONArray passed as argument; and a value greater than 0 if the size of this JSONObject is greater than the size of argument.

        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<JSONArray>
        Parameters:
        jsonArray - the JSONArray to be compared.
        Returns:
        a value less than 0 if the size of this JSONArray is less than the size of the JSONArray passed as argument; and a value greater than 0 if the size of this JSONObject is greater than the size of argument. Return 0 if this JSONArray size is equal to the argument JSONArray;

      • toReferencedTree

        public JSONArray toReferencedTree()
        Create a JSON structure where the the root array doesn't contain another object, instead of it contain the references to the objects. The reference is a field value of the object. The value of the property that has the object is replaced with the value of the object property marked like reference field. The reference field should not be an object or array.
        Returns:
        a new JSONArray structure with all the object referenced.

      • toReferencedElement

        public JSONArray toReferencedElement()
        Retrieve a referenced JSONArray. For a JSONArray the referenced element is the same as a referenced JSONArray, all the element of type JSONObject will be replaced by the reference.
        Specified by:
        toReferencedElement in class JSONElement
        Returns:
